<TEXT type="str">We live in a golden age of public speaking. The thing is, most speeches are delivered to small groups, and they are known as presentations or sales pitches. Scott Schwertly, founder and CEO of Ethos3 , a presentation design and training boutique in Nashville, Tennessee, offers a proprietary test to determine each individual’s strengths . By classifying you in one of several categories, from scholar to scientist to entertainer, Schwertly promises to hone your presentation skills. You can even become a well-rounded presenter by trying other personas. 
 
Related: 6 Tips to Be a More Confident Speaker 
 
What’s Your Presentation Persona? 
By Scott Schwertly and Sunday Mancini 
February; McGraw-Hill Education; $26 
 
This article originally appeared in the February 2017 issue of SUCCESS magazine .</TEXT> 
